# App Shell V2 — AI Setup Guide

This is a React design scaffold. The shell layer (sidebar, topbar, drawers) is pre-built and frozen.

---

## CRITICAL — Read this first

When someone says "set up my project" (or anything similar like "setup", "get started", "initialize"):

**DO NOT explore files. DO NOT run npm install. DO NOT start a dev server. DO NOT do anything technical.**

Your ONLY job is to have a short conversation — 4 questions — then make targeted file edits. Nothing else.

Start immediately with Q1. No preamble, no explanation, just ask the question.

---

## The 4 questions — ask one at a time, wait for the answer before asking the next

Run through these four questions **one at a time**. Do not ask them all at once.

---

### Q1 — Project name
Ask: "What's your project name?"

Store the answer as PROJECT_NAME.

---

### Q2 — What they're building
Ask: "Describe what you're building in one line."

Use keyword matching to determine CONTEXT and VARIANT:

**Settings context** (sidebar: settings) — if the description contains any of:
settings, config, configuration, integrations, billing, phone, payments, account, preferences, admin, system, manage, setup, permissions, compliance, security, profile, business

→ Within settings, pick VARIANT:
- Has keywords: tabs, sections, numbers, compliance, messaging, regulatory, voice → `settings-tabbed`
- Has keywords: course, membership, detail, drill, sub-page, vertical → `settings-vertical-tabs`
- Default settings → `settings-simple`

**Main nav context** (sidebar: main-nav) — everything else (default fallback)

→ Within main nav, pick VARIANT:
- Has keywords: tabs, sections, overview + detail, analytics, campaigns, multiple views → `main-nav-tabbed`
- Has keywords: detail, drill-down, contact, record, profile page → `main-nav-vertical-tabs`
- Default → `main-nav-simple`

---

### Q3 — Optional PRD
Ask: "Do you have a PRD or product description? Paste it here, or press Enter to skip."

If provided, re-run the same keyword matching against the full PRD text to refine CONTEXT and VARIANT. A longer description gives more signal — trust it over Q2 if they conflict.

---

### Q4 — Confirm
Ask: "Got it. I'll set up [PROJECT_NAME] as a [VARIANT description in plain English]. Ready to go? (Y/n)"

On Y — make all the changes below. On N — stop and ask what they'd like to change.

---

## Changes to make after confirmation

### 1. `package.json`
Change `"name"` to kebab-case of PROJECT_NAME.
Example: "Social Planner" → `"social-planner"`

### 2. `index.html`
Change `<title>My Project</title>` to `<title>PROJECT_NAME</title>`

### 3. `src/pages/Page1.jsx`
Rename the file to a short meaningful name based on PROJECT_NAME.
Example: "Social Planner" → `Overview.jsx`

Replace its content with the correct AppShell variant template from the section below.

### 4. `src/App.jsx`
Update the import and route:
- Change `import Page1 from './pages/Page1'` to the new filename
- Change `<Route path="/" element={<Page1 />} />` to match

---

## AppShell variant templates

Use these exactly. Replace PROJECT_NAME with the actual name. Tell the teammate where to add their content (the Canvas block).

---

### main-nav-simple (default fallback)
For: dashboards, single-screen products, simple overviews

```jsx
import { LayoutDashboard, FileText, Settings } from 'lucide-react'
import AppShell from '../shell/AppShell'
import Canvas from '../shell/Canvas'

const NAV_SECTIONS = [
  {
    items: [
      { icon: LayoutDashboard, label: 'Overview', active: true },
      { icon: FileText, label: 'Page 2' },
      { icon: Settings, label: 'Page 3' },
    ],
  },
]

export default function Overview() {
  return (
    <AppShell
      sidebar="main-nav"
      sidebarProps={{ navSections: NAV_SECTIONS }}
      topbar="simple"
      topbarProps={{ title: 'PROJECT_NAME' }}
    >
      <Canvas level={1}>
        {/* Your content goes here */}
      </Canvas>
    </AppShell>
  )
}
```

---

### main-nav-tabbed
For: products with multiple sections and sub-tabs (e.g. Social Listening, Marketing)

```jsx
import { useState } from 'react'
import { LayoutDashboard, FileText, Settings } from 'lucide-react'
import AppShell from '../shell/AppShell'
import Canvas from '../shell/Canvas'

const NAV_SECTIONS = [
  {
    items: [
      { icon: LayoutDashboard, label: 'Overview', active: true },
      { icon: FileText, label: 'Page 2' },
      { icon: Settings, label: 'Page 3' },
    ],
  },
]

const SECTION_TABS = ['Section 1', 'Section 2', 'Section 3']
const SUB_TABS = ['Tab 1', 'Tab 2', 'Tab 3']

export default function Overview() {
  const [activeSubTab, setActiveSubTab] = useState('Tab 1')

  return (
    <AppShell
      sidebar="main-nav"
      sidebarProps={{ navSections: NAV_SECTIONS }}
      topbar="tabbed"
      topbarProps={{
        title: 'PROJECT_NAME',
        sectionTabs: SECTION_TABS,
        activeSection: 'Section 1',
        subTabs: SUB_TABS,
        activeSubTab,
        onSubTabChange: setActiveSubTab,
      }}
    >
      <Canvas level={1}>
        {/* Your content goes here */}
      </Canvas>
    </AppShell>
  )
}
```

---

### main-nav-vertical-tabs
For: detail/drill-down pages with side navigation (e.g. contact detail, record page)

```jsx
import { useState } from 'react'
import { LayoutDashboard, FileText, Settings } from 'lucide-react'
import AppShell from '../shell/AppShell'
import Canvas from '../shell/Canvas'

const NAV_SECTIONS = [
  {
    items: [
      { icon: LayoutDashboard, label: 'Overview', active: true },
      { icon: FileText, label: 'Page 2' },
      { icon: Settings, label: 'Page 3' },
    ],
  },
]

const SIDE_TABS = ['Overview', 'Details', 'Activity', 'Notes']

export default function Overview() {
  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState('Overview')

  return (
    <AppShell
      sidebar="main-nav"
      sidebarProps={{ navSections: NAV_SECTIONS }}
      topbar="simple"
      topbarProps={{ title: 'PROJECT_NAME' }}
      backToolbar={{ onBack: () => {}, label: 'Back' }}
      verticalTabs={{
        tabs: SIDE_TABS,
        activeTab,
        onTabChange: setActiveTab,
      }}
    >
      <Canvas level={1}>
        {/* Your content goes here */}
      </Canvas>
    </AppShell>
  )
}
```

---

### settings-simple
For: a single settings page with no sub-sections

```jsx
import { Building2, Users, CreditCard, Settings } from 'lucide-react'
import AppShell from '../shell/AppShell'
import Canvas from '../shell/Canvas'

const SECTIONS = [
  {
    label: 'General',
    items: [
      { icon: Building2, label: 'Business profile', active: true },
      { icon: Users, label: 'Team' },
      { icon: CreditCard, label: 'Billing' },
      { icon: Settings, label: 'Preferences' },
    ],
  },
]

export default function Overview() {
  return (
    <AppShell
      sidebar="settings"
      sidebarProps={{ sections: SECTIONS, onBack: () => {} }}
      topbar="simple"
      topbarProps={{ title: 'PROJECT_NAME' }}
    >
      <Canvas level={1}>
        {/* Your content goes here */}
      </Canvas>
    </AppShell>
  )
}
```

---

### settings-tabbed
For: settings with multiple sections and sub-tabs (e.g. Phone System, Messaging Limits)

```jsx
import { useState } from 'react'
import { Building2, Users, CreditCard, Settings } from 'lucide-react'
import AppShell from '../shell/AppShell'
import Canvas from '../shell/Canvas'

const SECTIONS = [
  {
    label: 'General',
    items: [
      { icon: Building2, label: 'Business profile' },
      { icon: Users, label: 'Team' },
      { icon: CreditCard, label: 'Billing', active: true },
      { icon: Settings, label: 'Preferences' },
    ],
  },
]

const SECTION_TABS = ['Section 1', 'Section 2', 'Section 3']
const SUB_TABS = ['Tab 1', 'Tab 2', 'Tab 3']

export default function Overview() {
  const [activeSubTab, setActiveSubTab] = useState('Tab 1')

  return (
    <AppShell
      sidebar="settings"
      sidebarProps={{ sections: SECTIONS, onBack: () => {} }}
      topbar="tabbed"
      topbarProps={{
        title: 'PROJECT_NAME',
        sectionTabs: SECTION_TABS,
        activeSection: 'Section 1',
        subTabs: SUB_TABS,
        activeSubTab,
        onSubTabChange: setActiveSubTab,
      }}
    >
      <Canvas level={1}>
        {/* Your content goes here */}
      </Canvas>
    </AppShell>
  )
}
```

---

### settings-vertical-tabs
For: settings detail page with side navigation (e.g. Memberships, course builder)

```jsx
import { useState } from 'react'
import { Building2, Users, CreditCard, Settings } from 'lucide-react'
import AppShell from '../shell/AppShell'
import Canvas from '../shell/Canvas'

const SECTIONS = [
  {
    label: 'General',
    items: [
      { icon: Building2, label: 'Business profile', active: true },
      { icon: Users, label: 'Team' },
      { icon: CreditCard, label: 'Billing' },
      { icon: Settings, label: 'Preferences' },
    ],
  },
]

const SIDE_TABS = ['Overview', 'Details', 'Settings', 'Activity']

export default function Overview() {
  const [activeTab, setActiveTab] = useState('Overview')

  return (
    <AppShell
      sidebar="settings"
      sidebarProps={{ sections: SECTIONS, onBack: () => {} }}
      topbar="simple"
      topbarProps={{ title: 'PROJECT_NAME' }}
      backToolbar={{ onBack: () => {}, label: 'Back' }}
      verticalTabs={{
        tabs: SIDE_TABS,
        activeTab,
        onTabChange: setActiveTab,
      }}
    >
      <Canvas level={1}>
        {/* Your content goes here */}
      </Canvas>
    </AppShell>
  )
}
```

---

## Frozen files — never modify

These are the shell layer. Teammates never touch them:

```
src/shell/AppShell.jsx
src/shell/Sidebar.jsx
src/shell/TopBar.jsx
src/shell/Canvas.jsx
src/shell/BackToolbar.jsx
src/shell/VerticalTabs.jsx
src/shell/HelpDrawer.jsx
src/shell/NotificationsDrawer.jsx
src/shell/SubAccountSwitcher.jsx
src/index.css
```

---

## Where teammates work

All design work lives in `src/pages/`. Each screen or feature is a new `.jsx` file. The teammate never needs to open any other folder.

When they ask "how do I add a new page", create a new file in `src/pages/` using the same AppShell variant as their existing page, and add a route in `src/App.jsx`.

---

## Reference variants (for your own reference, not for teammates)

All shell variants are accessible at `/ref/*` in the browser:
- /ref/main-nav-simple
- /ref/main-nav-tabbed
- /ref/main-nav-tabbed-vertical-tabs
- /ref/main-nav-vertical-tabs-back-toolbar
- /ref/level2
- /ref/fullscreen-builder
- /ref/settings-tabbed
- /ref/settings-vertical-tabs
- /ref/settings-vertical-tabs-back-toolbar
- /ref/fullscreen-vertical-tabs-back-toolbar
